bubba-backend (1.2.0.33) karmic; urgency=low

  * Changing order for RAID creation, to work as much as possible with
    external disk before doing anything with the internal disk. So if
    the action on the external disk fails, it will not affect the running
    system. This includes eventual unmounting and fstab-removal of the 
    external disk, and the repartition of the external disk.

 -- Carl Fürstenberg <carl@excito.com>  Fri, 21 Aug 2009 16:31:05 +0200

